 Lawson does a Woolmer
LOKENDRA PRATAP SAHI LawsonNew Delhi: Geoff Lawson has done a Bob Woolmer.Indeed, the 49-year-old Australian has also chosen to stay in the Pakistan Cricket Boards National Academy, just off the Gaddafi in Lahore. Its convenient Everythings there Im comfortable staying at the Academy, Pakistans newest coach told The Telegraph on Thursday. The late Woolmer, it may be recalled, had made the Academy his home instead of either staying in a hotel (like Greg Chappell in Bangalore) or in an apartment (like Dav Whatmore in Dhaka). Lawson, who got the job in July, is on a two-year contract. 
